{"atom_id": "ig34_p0218_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 218, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.3 Cell Phenotype Findings (CP)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| 3 | ABC-123 | CP | ABC0-001-001 | 3 | YGOCC | Target Occupancy | CD16 BINDING MOLECULE | ANTI-CDxx ANTIBODY | MONOCYTES | FSC SSC(CD45+CD14+(CD16+HLADRhi | PROINFLAMMATORY MONOCYTES | FSC SSC(CD45+CD14+(CD16+HLADRhi | TARGET ENGAGEMENT | RECEPTOR OCCUPANCY | MONOCYTE CELL CD16 RO | 83 | % | QUANTITATIVE | NUMBER FRACTION | 83 | 83 | % | BLOOD | FLOW CYTOMETRY | 2020-07- 24T09:00 |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10_R15_NEW1_NEW7_round3_batch22b", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0218_a006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 218, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.3 Cell Phenotype Findings (CP)", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "Example 8", "heading_level": 6, "sibling_index": 8, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10_R15_NEW1_NEW7_round3_batch22b", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0218_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 218, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.3 Cell Phenotype Findings (CP)", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The example is a use case for data from a receptor occupancy study based on a direct cell-binding assay method to illustrate the use of several new variables.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10_R15_NEW1_NEW7_round3_batch22b", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0218_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 218, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.3 Cell Phenotype Findings (CP)", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "In the example, target engagement is assessed by measuring the extent to which a cell-associated target protein (the hypothetical cell marker CDxx) is occupied by a therapeutic antibody (CDxx antibody) intended to interact with it.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10_R15_NEW1_NEW7_round3_batch22b", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0218_a009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 218, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.3 Cell Phenotype Findings (CP)", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The assay uses a labeled detection antibody to the therapeutic antibody to measure the proportion of the target bound by the therapeutic antibody in an unaltered specimen (numerator), as compared to the total amount of target available for binding (denominator).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10_R15_NEW1_NEW7_round3_batch22b", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0218_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 218, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.3 Cell Phenotype Findings (CP)", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The total target available for binding is assessed by saturating the specimen with the therapeutic antibody before measuring the labeled detection antibody.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10_R15_NEW1_NEW7_round3_batch22b", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0218_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 218, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.3 Cell Phenotype Findings (CP)", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "To correct the numerator and denominator for non-specific (background) binding, labeled isotype controls are included which are subtracted to yield specific binding values.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10_R15_NEW1_NEW7_round3_batch22b", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0218_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 218, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.3 Cell Phenotype Findings (CP)", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Although sponsors may elect to only report the final calculated receptor occupancy (proportion of bound/total target occupied) as in Example 7, this example includes the various measured parameters generated in the assay which are then used to make calculations for the final Receptor Occupancy value.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10_R15_NEW1_NEW7_round3_batch22b", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0218_a013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 218, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.3 Cell Phenotype Findings (CP)", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Since the example is measuring binding and not a cell population per se, the Sublineage Marker String (CPSBMRKS), Cell State (CPCELSTA), and Cell State Marker String (CPCSMRKS) are not used and are not included.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10_R15_NEW1_NEW7_round3_batch22b", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0218_a014", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 218, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.3 Cell Phenotype Findings (CP)", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Other variables such as CPMRKSTR, CPGATE, and CPGATEDEF are used to identify the cell population on which the binding of interest was measured.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10_R15_NEW1_NEW7_round3_batch22b", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0218_a015", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 218, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.3 Cell Phenotype Findings (CP)", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "In addition, the Sponsor Test Description (CPSPTSTD) and Test Panel (CPTSTPNL) variables may be helpful for identifying a specific cell population.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10_R15_NEW1_NEW7_round3_batch22b", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0218_a016", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 218, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.3 Cell Phenotype Findings (CP)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Rows 1-3:\tIllustrate how the test name (CPTEST), marker string (CPMRKSTR), binding agent (CPBDAGNT), replicates (CPREPNUM), and summary result type (CPCOLSRT) are populated for data from an assay used to assess target engagement by measuring the occupancy of the CDxx cell-associated target protein expressed on cytotoxic T-lymphocytes (defined as CD45+CD3+CD8+CDxx+). In this direct assay, CPBDAGNT identifies the CDxx antibody (therapeutic antibody) as the target-bound substance of interest. Two replicate determinations and the mean extent of CDxx bound in the unaltered specimen are indicated using CPREPNUM and CPCOLSRT.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10_R15_NEW1_NEW7_round3_batch22b", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0218_a017", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 218, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.3 Cell Phenotype Findings (CP)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Rows 4-6:\tCPTEST, CPBDAGNT, REPNUM, and CPCOLSRT are used the same manner as they are in rows 1-3, except that CPTSTCND is now also used to indicate that the assay was conducted under a saturating condition of CDxx antibody by adding an excess of this therapeutic antibody to the assay system. Under this condition, the labeled detection antibody reflects the maximum (total) amount of CDxx available to be occupied by the therapeutic antibody,", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10_R15_NEW1_NEW7_round3_batch22b", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0218_a018", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 218, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.3 Cell Phenotype Findings (CP)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Rows 7-8:\tShow values for background (i.e. non-specific) binding of the labeled detection antibody to the CDxx-expressing cells of interest by using an isotype control belonging to the same immunoglobulin class/subclass as the therapeutic antibody. This is indicated in CPBDAGNT and is also shown for how the sponsor chose to represent it in CPMRKSTR.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10_R15_NEW1_NEW7_round3_batch22b", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0218_a019", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 218, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.3 Cell Phenotype Findings (CP)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Rows 9-11:\tRows 9 and 10 show values for specific binding of the therapeutic antibody (CDxx antibody) in the unaltered (native) specimen (Row 9) and the specimen to which excess CDxx antibody was added (saturated assay condition) (Row 10). Specific binding was determined by subtracting the appropriate background measured in Rows 7 and 8 from the mean target bound (Row 3) and mean target total (Row 6). Row 11 shows the final result for CDxx antibody occupancy on the CDxx target protein as the quotient of the specific binding in the native specimen (Row 9) to the specific binding measuring the total CDxx available for binding (Row 10).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10_R15_NEW1_NEW7_round3_batch22b", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
